# Design System Guide

## When to Activate
- Creating a new design system for a project (designer)
- Defining design tokens (colors, spacing, typography)
- Scaffolding reusable UI components
- Mapping design tokens to Tailwind/CSS variables
- Establishing visual consistency standards

## Deliverables

### 1. Design Tokens (`src/styles/tokens.ts`)
- Primary, Secondary, Neutral color palette (50~900 scale)
- Semantic colors (error, warning, success, info)
- Spacing scale (xs ~ 2xl)
- Typography (fontFamily, fontSize, fontWeight, lineHeight)
- Border radius, shadow scale

### 2. Tailwind/CSS Variable Mapping
- `tailwind.config.ts` extension or `src/styles/globals.css` CSS variables

### 3. Base Component Scaffolding

| Component | Variants |
|-----------|----------|
| Button | Primary, Secondary, Ghost, Destructive, each size (sm/md/lg) |
| Input | Text, Select, Checkbox, Radio, Textarea |
| Card | Default, Outlined, Elevated |
| Modal | Default, Confirm, Fullscreen |
| Toast | Success, Error, Warning, Info |
| Layout | Container, Stack (vertical/horizontal), Grid |

### 4. Spacing/Margin Guide (`docs/design-system.md`)

## Guidelines
1. The agent generates a code-based design system — not Figma mockups
2. All components must use design tokens — no hardcoded values
3. Components must be accessible (aria attributes, keyboard navigation)
4. Document token usage in `docs/design-system.md`

## Integration
- designer: Primary author
- frontend-dev: Consumes tokens and components
- visual-qa: Verifies compliance against tokens
